    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">旁邊</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>PLACE to the LEFT OR RIGHT, AND NOT IN FRONT OR BEHIND.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for the the place beside a person, a road, a river or anything else is páng 旁 and this word can occur after demonstrative pronouns like 其.</p>
<p>2. Cè 側 refers to anything that is beside something upright, like a building or a standing person, and the word can also be used independently unmodified by a preceding explicit indication of place..</p>
        </div>
